Package com.github.tommyettinger.ds.interop

Class ConversionToGDX

java.lang.Object
com.github.tommyettinger.ds.interop.ConversionToGDX
public class ConversionToGDX extends Object
Converts from arbitrary data structures that implement JDK interfaces to libGDX data structures (which typically implement Iterable at most). You can send JDK classes like ArrayList to methods in this to convert to Array or ObjectSet, just as you can send jdkgdxds classes like ObjectList.

      Can be used to convert from any Collection to a new Array of the same element type. This can take an ObjectList, ObjectSet, NumberedSet, or any JDK Collection, to name a few.
      Type Parameters:
      T - the element type for from and the result
      Parameters:
      from - a Collection from the JDK, jdkgdxds, or some other library
      Returns:
      a new Array of type T holding the items of from (this does not give a Class to the Array constructor)

    • toArrayMap

      public static <K, V> com.badlogic.gdx.utils.ArrayMap<K,V> toArrayMap(Map<? extends K,? extends V> from)
      Can be used to convert from any JDK Map to a new libGDX ArrayMap with the same key and value types. Note that jdkgdxds does not have a direct equivalent to libGDX's ArrayMap, because ArrayMap is only the "right choice" in some extremely narrow situations, and is only barely used inside libGDX (and only in its 3D code).
      Type Parameters:
      K - the key type
      V - the value type
      Parameters:
      from - a Map from the JDK, jdkgdxds, or some other library
      Returns:
      a new ArrayMap holding the keys and values of from (this does not give a Class to the ArrayMap constructor)

      Parameters:
      from - anything that implements the JDK Collection interface
      Returns:
      a new libGDX ObjectSet holding the unique items in from

      Can be used to convert from any JDK Map, such as a HashMap, ObjectObjectMap, or CaseInsensitiveOrderedMap, to a libGDX ObjectMap.

    • toIdentityMap

      public static <K, V> com.badlogic.gdx.utils.IdentityMap<K,V> toIdentityMap(Map<? extends K,? extends V> from)
      Can be used to convert from any JDK Map, such as a HashMap, IdentityObjectMap, or CaseInsensitiveOrderedMap, to a libGDX IdentityMap. In almost all cases, IdentityMap is more permissive about allowing duplicate keys, so converting to an IdentityMap should be lossless.
      Type Parameters:
      K - the type of keys; the same in from and the returned IdentityMap
      V - the type of values; the same in from and the returned IdentityMap
      Parameters:
      from - any Map that has a usable Map.keySet() method
      Returns:
      a new IdentityMap holding all of the key-value pairs in from

    • toQueue

      public static <T> com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Queue<T> toQueue(Collection<? extends T> from)
      Can be used to convert from any Collection to a new libGDX Queue of the same element type. This can take an ObjectList, ObjectSet, NumberedSet, or any JDK Collection, to name a few.
      Note that Queue in libGDX corresponds to ObjectDeque in jdkgdxds. Both are double-ended queues.
      Type Parameters:
      T - the element type for from and the result
      Parameters:
      from - a Collection from the JDK, jdkgdxds, or some other library
      Returns:
      a new Queue of type T holding the items of from (this does not give a Class to the Queue constructor)

      Parameters:
      from - a primitive-long-backed data structure from jdkgdxds
      Returns:
      a new LongQueue holding the items of from
